daily_summary.headline: Routine SpaceX Starlink Deployments Dominate the Day

top_events.title: Falcon 9 Block 5 | Starlink Group 17-19
top_events.description: SpaceX's Falcon 9 Block 5 is set to launch the Starlink Group 17-19 from Vandenberg SFB, CA, USA. This mission involves deploying a batch of Starlink satellites for global internet coverage.
top_events.action: Watch live stream for launch and deployment.

top_events.title: Electron | Bridging The Swarm (NeonSat-1A)
top_events.description: Rocket Lab's Electron rocket will launch the NeonSat-1A to test Earth observation capabilities for the South Korean government.
top_events.action: Follow updates and watch the launch online.

top_events.title: Falcon 9 Block 5 | Starlink Group 6-101
top_events.description: Another batch of Starlink satellites will be launched by SpaceX's Falcon 9 from Cape Canaveral SFS, FL, USA.
top_events.action: Tune in to the live stream for real-time coverage.
